<TITLE> Top lawyers' forum protests SC ruling </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 4 (bdnews24.com)The Supreme Court Bar Association (SCBA) on Monday protested the Supreme Court agreeing to considering admitting the BNP secretary general's petition against the High Court verdict that declared the fifth amendment of the constitution illegal. The top lawyer's forum rushed a meeting in Shamsul Haque Chowdhury hall with association president AFM Mezbahuddin in the chair and decided to form a 'strong panel' with senior lawyers to continue the legal battle to uphold the landmark judgement that decalred governments after Aug 15, 1975 illegitimate. The Supreme Court permitted Khandaker Delwar Hossain and three SC lawyers to file a leave to appeal within four weeks The amendment had given constitutional legitimacy to military governments after the 1975 assassination of independence hero president Sheikh Mujibur Rahman in a military coup. The lawyers also decided to petition the highest court to become a party to the case to see the High Court verdict upheld
